09:11 AM Defendant Mark F Froehlig in court with attorney Mark Emil Kershek.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Katrina Voge, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court conducts an initial appearance in 22CM604 and sets bond.
Cases 21CT849 and 22CF429 are called for plea and sentencing.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

In Case 21CT849: 
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
  Count 2 is Dismissed and read in.
  Count 3 is Dismissed by operation of law. 

In Case 22CF429: 
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
  Count 2 is Dismissed and read in.

Cases 22CM604, 22TR2240, 22TR2241, and 22TR2242 are Dismissed and read in. 
State and Defense make joint sentencing recommendations.
Defendant makes statement to the court. 

In Case 21CT849: 
Court orders the following:

SENTENCE WITHHELD.
Credit: 20 Days if revoked; 

Term of Probation:  2 YEARS; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Compliance with OWI Treatment Court contract and all conditions;
*No operation of a vehicle without a valid license;

CONDITION TIME: 100 DAYS, 1st 60 Days with Huber, Remaining 40 DAYS STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  
Defendant remanded into custody; 

D/L REVOCATION: 24 months.
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 24 months.

FINE: $2,302, included IID Surcharge; 
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $40 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Waukesha Memorial.  

All Fees/Fines/Surcharges are to be paid as a condition of probation or be converted to civil judgment for non-payment.
Cash on hand to be applied to Costs/Fines/Surcharches. 
